    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing free_uci_indication function to prevent memory leaks in UCI handling\n\n### Summary\nThe OpenAirInterface 5G codebase was missing a critical `free_uci_indication` function that should have been implemented in `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`. This function is needed to properly free memory allocated for UCI (Uplink Control Information) indications, particularly the dynamically allocated payload fields in FORMAT_2_3_4 PDU types.\n\nWithout this function, memory allocated for fields like `harq_payload`, `sr_payload`, `csi_part1_payload`, and `csi_part2_payload` was not being freed, leading to memory leaks under continuous UCI indication processing.\n\nThe issue was identified when analyzing the existing `phy_nr_uci_indication` functions in both the standard OAI implementation and the AERIAL integration, which allocate memory for these payload fields but lack corresponding cleanup code.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/inc/nr_fapi_p7_utils.h`: Created new header file declaring the `free_uci_indication` function\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Created new implementation file with proper memory freeing logic for all UCI PDU types\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/CMakeLists.txt`: Added the new source file to the build configuration\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/inc/nr_fapi.h`: Included the new header to make the function accessible\n\nThe implementation handles all three UCI PDU types and properly frees dynamically allocated memory while including defensive programming for different implementation variations. It follows the existing codebase patterns and includes proper NULL checks to prevent crashes.\n"
}